annotationA: Cell division cycle 5, isoform A; DNA binding; chromatin binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA splicing, via spliceosome; centrosome duplication
annotationB: DnaJ homolog subfamily C member 5 homolog; Cysteine string protein (Csp) is a synaptic vesicle-associated co-chaperone of Hsc70 that is vital for presynaptic proteostasis and maintenance of synaptic function. Csp protein substrates include SNARE proteins and shi, which mediate synaptic vesicle exo- and endocytosis respectively
